VINCULOS.OUTRAS-INFORMACOES:
Final evaluation of the EU-funded project ?Active citizenship networks: social protection, education, and citizens for an effective cooperation? (?Redes de Cidadania Activa: Protec&#807;a&#771;o Social, Educac&#807;a&#771;o e Cidada&#771;os para uma cooperac&#807;a&#771;o mais Eficiente?), implemented by the Italian NGO CIES. Main tasks included:
? Evaluation of results achieved in the period 2013 ? 2016 by local authorities and civil society organization dealing with social protection in 3 provinces in Angola;
? Needs assessment of Angolan Civil Society (CSOs and NGOs) and Local Authorities in the field of governance and social protection, children and adolescents' rights gender issues, and protection and promotion of human and social rights;
? Impact assessment of activities carried out by ?Rede de Protec&#807;a&#771;o da Crianc&#807;a? in Benguela and Kwanza Sul Provinces, namely: reactivation of the Networks and running activities in partnership with provinces and national INAC Offices, and dissemination of ?registro de nascimento? (Benguela Province), in partnership with the Diretoria Provincial de Justic&#807;a de Benguela/Conservato&#769;ria do registo civil;
? Identification of gaps and needs to be addressed by the project in its second phase, suggesting methodologies for future interventions by local partners and project stakeholders, specially in the field of children and adolescents' rights.
